MacOS Terminal (Command Line Interface)

To find out where we are in the terminal:
- pwd
- open /Users/AraavNayak/Desktop

To see what the directory has: use list command.
- ls

To move between directories (change directory):
- cd [directory]

To go back up to parent directory:
- cd ..

To switch to the current directory (no effect):
- cd .

To clear screen (pushes content up). Could also use Cmd+K
- clear

To switch to home directory:
- cd ~

To create a new file. This creates a new file in the current directory.
- touch test_file.txt

To open file:
- open test_file.txt

To make a directory (empty folder):
- mkdir test_directory

To remove file:
- rm test_file.txt